# Career-Copilot — Cursor Instructions

> AI-powered job search pipeline: offer evaluation, CV generation, pipeline tracking, portal scanning, batch processing, interview preparation.
>
> This file is the primary instruction set for Cursor when operating inside this repository.

---

## 1. Origin & Purpose

This repository is an **AI-driven career operations pipeline** designed to run through AI CLIs. Workflows are shared across providers; only tool names differ by CLI.

---

## 2. Data Contract

All files fall into exactly one of two layers. **Never violate the boundary.**

### User Layer — NEVER auto-update

`cv.md`, `config/profile.yml`, `modes/_profile.md`, `article-digest.md`, `portals.yml`, `data/*`, `reports/*`, `output/*`, `interview-prep/*`

### System Layer — safe to auto-update

`modes/_shared.md`, `modes/*.md` (except `_profile.md`), `templates/*`, scripts (`*.mjs`, `scripts/*.mjs`), and instruction files (`.github/copilot-instructions.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `GEMINI.md`, `.cursor/rules/*`, `.windsurfrules`).

### The Golden Rule

> User customizations go ONLY in `modes/_profile.md` and `config/profile.yml`.

---

## 3. Main Files Reference

- `cv.md` is the canonical source for CV content
- `article-digest.md` is proof-point source
- `data/applications.md` is the tracker
- `modes/*.md` define workflows

---

## 4. Update Check

On the first message of each session, run:

```bash
node update-system.mjs check
```

If `update-available`, ask before applying updates.

---

## 5. First Run Onboarding

Before first use, verify:
1. `cv.md`
2. `config/profile.yml`
3. `modes/_profile.md`
4. `portals.yml`
5. `data/applications.md`
6. `data/pipeline.md`

If missing, guide the user through setup incrementally.

---

## 6. Skill Modes — Intent Routing

Route user requests to mode files under `modes/`:
- Job URL/JD text → `modes/auto-pipeline.md`
- "Evaluate" → `modes/evaluate.md`
- "Batch" → `modes/batch.md`
- "Pipeline" → `modes/pipeline.md`
- "Scan" → `modes/scan.md`
- "Compare" → `modes/compare.md`
- "PDF/CV" → `modes/pdf.md`
- "Tracker" → `modes/tracker.md`
- "Interview" → `modes/interview-prep.md`
- "Contact" → `modes/contact.md`
- "Deep research" → `modes/deep.md`
- "Training" → `modes/training.md`
- "Project" → `modes/project.md`

Always read `modes/_shared.md` and `modes/_profile.md` first.

---

## 7. CV Source of Truth

- Never invent metrics or experience.
- Tailor from `cv.md` and `article-digest.md` only.
- Ask user for missing numbers.

---

## 8. Ethical Use

- Quality over quantity.
- Never submit on behalf of user.
- Discourage low-fit (<4.0/5) applications with explicit tradeoffs.
- Keep scoring transparent.

---

## 9. Offer Verification — MANDATORY

Prefer Playwright for job liveness verification:
1. Navigate
2. Snapshot
3. Confirm JD content + apply action

If unavailable in batch workers, use HTTP fetch fallback and mark verification as unconfirmed.

---

## 10. Stack & Conventions

- Node.js ESM scripts (`*.mjs`)
- Playwright for PDF + dynamic page extraction
- YAML config
- Markdown/TSV data
- Report naming: `{num}-{slug}-{date}.md`

---

## 11. TSV Format for Tracker Additions

Use this row shape in `data/applications.md`:

```
| {num} | {date} | {company} | {role} | {score}/5 | {status} | {pdf_emoji} | [{num}](reports/{num}-{slug}-{date}.md) | {note} |
```

For batch TSV fragments, use tab-separated 9-column rows in `batch/tracker-additions/`.

---

## 12. Canonical Application States

Allowed states only:
`Evaluated`, `Applied`, `Responded`, `Interview`, `Offer`, `Rejected`, `Discarded`, `SKIP`

---

## 13. Tool Mapping by CLI

The mode files express **semantic operations**. Map them to provider tools using this adapter table.

| Concept | GitHub Copilot CLI | Claude Code | Gemini CLI | Cursor | Windsurf |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| sub_agent | `task` | `Task` | Provider task/agent primitive | Agent/composer task | Cascade task/workflow |
| web_fetch | `web_fetch` | `WebFetch` | HTTP fetch tool | Fetch/integrated browser fetch | Fetch tool |
| web_search | `web_search` | `WebSearch` | Search tool | Web search | Web search |
| file_read | `view` | `Read` | File read tool | File read | File read |
| file_write | `create` | `Write` | File write tool | File create/write | File write |
| file_edit | `edit` | `Edit` | File edit tool | File edit | File edit |
| shell | `bash` | `Bash` | Shell tool | Terminal command | Terminal command |
| browser_navigate/snapshot/click | `browser_*` (Playwright MCP) | Browser MCP tools | Browser/automation tools | Built-in browser/automation | Built-in browser/automation |

### Semantic tool concepts

- `sub_agent`: delegate complex/parallel work
- `web_fetch`: fetch static web data
- `web_search`: search the web
- `browser_navigate`, `browser_snapshot`, `browser_click`: dynamic browser automation
- `file_read`, `file_write`, `file_edit`: filesystem ops
- `shell`: command execution

When a provider lacks a capability, use the fallback policy in section 17.

---

## 14. Personalization

User-specific customization belongs in:
- `config/profile.yml`
- `modes/_profile.md`
- `article-digest.md`

Never put user-specific preferences in `modes/_shared.md`.

---

## 15. Language Modes

Use translated modes when targeting non-English markets. Default is `modes/` (English).

---

## 16. Workflow Quick Reference

Auto-pipeline:
1. Extract JD
2. Evaluate
3. Write report
4. Generate PDF (if worth applying)
5. Update tracker

Batch:
1. Read inputs
2. Process with sub-agents when available
3. Merge tracker additions
4. Summarize outcomes

---

## 17. Capability Fallback Policy

- If `sub_agent` is unavailable: process items sequentially in current context.
- If dynamic browser tools are unavailable: use static fetch and mark verification as unconfirmed.
- If provider-specific tool names differ: use semantic concepts from section 13.

- Use Cursor rules/composer capabilities to map semantic tool concepts.

---

## 18. Session Startup Checklist

1. Run update check
2. Verify onboarding files
3. Read profile (`config/profile.yml`)
4. Read shared rules (`modes/_shared.md`)
5. Read user overrides (`modes/_profile.md`)
6. Check tracker (`data/applications.md`)
7. Route intent to mode

---

## 19. Report & Output Structure

Report file: `reports/{num}-{slug}-{date}.md`
Output PDF: `output/{num}-{slug}-{date}.pdf`

---

## 20. Important Reminders

- Read mode files before executing.
- Always use canonical states.
- Always zero-pad report numbers.
- Always use ISO dates.
- Always check duplicates before tracker insertions.
- Always present results for user review.
